How to add new papers:

The site looks for papers in a Papers/ folder in your GitHub repo. There are two ways it discovers them:

Option 1 — Papers/index.json (recommended) Create a file at Papers/index.json listing your papers:
json

[
  { "key": "kt_paper1", "name": "MBChB Year 1 — Knowledge Test — Paper 1", "filename": "kt_paper1.json", "type": "kt" },
  { "key": "kt_paper2", "name": "MBChB Year 1 — Knowledge Test — Paper 2", "filename": "kt_paper2.json", "type": "kt" },
  { "key": "anat_paper1", "name": "MBChB Year 1 — Anatomy Exam — Paper 1",  "filename": "anat_paper1.json", "type": "anat" }
]

type must be "kt" (100 min, 72+8) or "anat" (45 min, 40+5).

Option 2 — Auto-discovery via GitHub API If there's no index.json, the app queries the GitHub API for all .json files in Papers/ and uses their filenames as paper names. Less control over display names.

Each paper file (e.g. Papers/kt_paper1.json) is a JSON array of question objects:
json

[
  {
    "id": "q1",
    "type": "sba",
    "topic": "SL-CV",
    "stem": "A 65-year-old presents with...",
    "options": ["Option A", "Option B", "Option C", "Option D", "Option E"],
    "correct": 2,
    "explanation": "Option C is correct because..."
  },
  {
    "id": "q73",
    "type": "vsaq",
    "topic": "Anat",
    "stem": "Name the nerve that supplies...",
    "answer": "The femoral nerve",
    "explanation": "Optional explanation here"
  }
]

    correct is the zero-based index of the correct option (0=A, 1=B, 2=C…)
    topic must match one of the keys in TOPIC_LABELS in the HTML (e.g. "SL-CV", "BIM-Cardio", "Anat", etc.)
    images is an optional array of URLs: "images": ["https://..."]

