Now here's the AI paper-writing prompt:
AI Instructions — Writing a Paper JSON File

Save this as your prompt to any AI (Claude, GPT, etc.) when you want a paper generated:

    You are writing a medical exam paper for MBChB Year 1 students at a UK medical school. Output a single valid JSON array — nothing else, no explanation, no markdown fences. The array must contain exactly [N] questions: [X] SBAs followed by [Y] VSAQs.

    Topic distribution — spread SBAs across these topic codes (use the exact keys): BIM-Cardio, BIM-Cells, BIM-Loco, BIM-Nerv, SL-CV, SL-Resp, SL-Repro, SL-Nutr, I-MCT, I-Imm, I-Inf, I-Can, KCP, Ethics, Pharm, REBM, Anat

    SBA format:
    json

    {
      "id": "q1",
      "type": "sba",
      "topic": "SL-CV",
      "stem": "A 68-year-old man presents with...\n\nWhat is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "options": ["Option A", "Option B", "Option C", "Option D", "Option E"],
      "correct": 2,
      "explanation": "Option C is correct because..."
    }

        id must be unique strings: "q1", "q2", etc.
        correct is zero-based index (0 = A, 1 = B, 2 = C, 3 = D, 4 = E)
        Always 5 options (A–E)
        Stem should be a realistic clinical vignette with age, sex, presenting complaint, relevant history/examination findings, and a clear lead-in question
        Distractors must be plausible — avoid obviously wrong options
        explanation must explain why the correct answer is right AND why the main distractor is wrong

    VSAQ format:
    json

    {
      "id": "q73",
      "type": "vsaq",
      "topic": "Anat",
      "stem": "A patient has a fracture of the surgical neck of the humerus.\n\nName the nerve most at risk of injury.",
      "answer": "Axillary nerve",
      "explanation": "The axillary nerve winds around the surgical neck of the humerus and is vulnerable to injury here."
    }

        VSAQs are short-answer; answer should be 1–3 sentences maximum
        No options or correct field

    Rules:

        Every id must be unique across the whole array
        Do not repeat questions from previous papers
        Difficulty should be appropriate for end of Year 1 (pre-clinical) — not clinical specialist level
        Avoid trick questions; test understanding not trivia
        For Pharm questions, focus on drug classes, mechanisms, and key adverse effects rather than specific doses
        REBM questions should test study design, statistics, and evidence interpretation
        Output raw JSON only — the file will be parsed directly by the exam platform

Fill in: [N] = total questions, [X] = SBA count, [Y] = VSAQ count. For a Knowledge Test use 72 SBA + 8 VSAQ. For Anatomy use 40 SBA + 5 VSAQ.

To add the paper to the site:

    Save the output as e.g. kt_paper2.json in your repo's Papers/ folder
    Add it to Papers/index.json:

json

{ "key": "kt_paper2", "name": "MBChB Year 1 — Knowledge Test — Paper 2", "filename": "kt_paper2.json", "type": "kt" }

    Commit and push — it appears immediately on the site

